description: A 6th/7th CE rectangular structure identified inside a settlement-cemetery, tentaively interpreted as an early wooden church.
bibliography: Lehane, J, and F Delaney. “A Cashel and a Burial Ground at Owenbristy, Co. Galway (E3770) : Eachtra Archaeological Projects.” Eachtra 8 (2010). http://eachtra.ie/index.php/journal/e3770-owenbristy-co-galway/.
